## Vercel Web Analytics Configuration - Status Report

### Summary
Vercel Web Analytics is **already fully installed and configured** in this project. After fetching the latest documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart, I verified that the existing implementation matches the official Next.js App Router integration exactly.

### Current Configuration

**Package Installation:**
- ✅ `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1 is installed in package.json
- ✅ All dependencies installed successfully via npm

**Integration:**
- ✅ Analytics component imported from `@vercel/analytics/next` in `app/src/app/layout.tsx`
- ✅ `<Analytics />` component properly placed inside `<body>` tag in root layout
- ✅ Implementation follows official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router

**Verification:**
- ✅ Build completed successfully (`npm run build`)
- ✅ Linter passed with no errors (`npm run lint`)
- ✅ Lock file (package-lock.json) is up-to-date

### Files Reviewed
- `app/package.json` - Contains @vercel/analytics dependency
- `app/src/app/layout.tsx` - Contains Analytics component integration
- `app/package-lock.json` - Up-to-date with dependencies

### Documentation Reference
According to the latest Vercel documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart), the Next.js App Router integration requires:
1. Installing `@vercel/analytics` package ✅
2. Importing from `@vercel/analytics/next` ✅
3. Adding `<Analytics />` component in the root layout's body ✅

All requirements are met.

### Next Steps for User
To complete the setup:
1. **Enable Analytics in Vercel Dashboard:** Navigate to your project in the Vercel dashboard and click the "Enable" button in the Analytics section
2. **Deploy:** Run `vercel deploy` or push to your connected Git repository to deploy
3. **Verify:** After deployment, check the browser Network tab for a Fetch/XHR request from `/<unique-path>/view` when visiting pages

### Notes
No code changes were made as the implementation was already correct and complete. The project is ready for deployment with Vercel Web Analytics enabled.
